# History: python-import-patterns-and-compatibility-guards

## v1.6.0 (2026-06-24)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1512 — implementation PLAN for an `[S14 API Design]` audit finding that `hephaestus/__init__.py` implements the PEP 562 `__getattr__` lazy loader but omits the companion module-level `__dir__()`, so `dir(hephaestus)` shows only ~4 eagerly-bound names and the entire lazily-loaded public API is invisible to introspection tools (IPython tab-completion, IDEs, doc generators).
**Verification:** **unverified** for ALL new material (section H + the new "Use when"/"When to Use" trigger + 3 new Failed Attempts rows + the new Verified On row). The plan's `__dir__()` edit and `TestDirDiscoverability` tests were never executed in CI. All pre-existing sections retain their prior verification levels (verified-ci for function-local / version-guard / Windows-guard / lazy-exports; verified-local for the surface-pin-stale fix and the access-time deprecation-warning implementation; unverified planning-guidance for section G).

### What changed

- Added a 9th "Use when" trigger to the frontmatter description and a 9th "When to Use" bullet: PLANNING the companion module-level `__dir__()` for a PEP 562 lazy-loader package whose `dir(pkg)` shows only eagerly-bound names.
- Added detailed-steps subsection **H. Adding the companion `__dir__()` to a PEP 562 lazy-loader package — UNVERIFIED planning-guidance**, with an `unverified` banner and five points: (1) a custom `__dir__` REPLACES (does not merge with) the default listing, so `set(globals())` MUST be folded into the return or `dir()` silently SHRINKS (drops `__version__`/`__author__`/dunders/already-cached lazy names); (2) `__dir__` returns names only and performs NO attribute access, so a deprecated lazy shim can be listed without firing its `DeprecationWarning` (cross-referenced to section F); (3) pin by SUBSET invariant (`set(_LAZY_IMPORTS) <= set(dir(pkg))`), never a hardcoded count; (4) regression-test that `dir()` does not SHRINK the visible set; (5) audit-snapshot counts drift (the audit's "35 symbols" was already stale at 40 on disk) — verify the live surface before quoting any count.
- Added 3 Failed Attempts rows (all `unverified`): returned only `sorted(set(_LAZY_IMPORTS) | set(__all__))` from `__dir__` (dropped `globals()` → `dir()` shrank); trusted the audit's "35 symbols" count (live = 40, a hardcoded-count test would be born stale); worried that listing a deprecated shim in `__dir__` would fire its `DeprecationWarning` (it doesn't — names only, no access).
- Added a Verified On row for issue #1512 marked **PLAN ONLY / unverified**.
- Updated the Overview verification row to append the section H `unverified` planning-guidance clause (without downgrading any existing verified section).
- Added tags: `dir`, `__dir__`, `discoverability`, `introspection`.
- Bumped version 1.5.0 → 1.6.0; date stays 2026-06-24.

### Why

The skill already taught the PEP 562 `__getattr__` lazy-loader seam (section B for widening the surface, section F for the access-time `DeprecationWarning`). Section F covers `__getattr__` (the resolve/access half of PEP 562); issue #1512's planning surfaced the natural sibling — the `__dir__` (discoverability/listing) half — which the prior sections did not cover and which shares this skill's exact search surface (`__getattr__`, lazy loader, PEP 562). Five durable, transferable lessons emerged: a custom module `__dir__` REPLACES the default listing rather than merging, so `set(globals())` must be folded in or the visible surface silently shrinks (the single most easily-missed point); `__dir__` returns names only and triggers no attribute access, so a deprecated lazy shim is listed without firing its access-time warning (directly connecting to section F); the contract must be pinned by a subset invariant, not a hardcoded count (the audit's "35 symbols" was already stale at 40 — the same staleness failure mode as the strict-equality `__all__` pins in sections B/B′); the primary failure mode is shrinkage, so a dedicated "does not shrink" regression test is warranted; and audit-snapshot counts drift between finding-time and fix-time. The plan was not executed, so all new material is `unverified` and section H carries an explicit unverified banner.

