### What changed

- Added a 7th "Use when" trigger to the frontmatter description and a 7th "When to Use" bullet: planning a DeprecationWarning at ACCESS time (not just call time) for a deprecated lazy shim behind a PEP 562 `__getattr__` loader.
- Added a new detailed-steps subsection **F. Proposed Workflow — planning an access-time DeprecationWarning across the PEP 562 lazy-loader seam (UNVERIFIED)** with a warning banner and 7 steps: grep the symbol before trusting the issue's structural claim (issue said `__all__`, reality is `_LAZY_IMPORTS`); keep access-time and call-time warnings as complementary layers; `module.__dict__.pop(name)` to defeat PEP 562 globals caching in the regression test; grep + rewrite stale-tolerant tests that document the silent resolve; update `COMPATIBILITY.md` prose in the same PR; re-confirm the import-surface boundary tests; validate `stacklevel` for an attribute-lookup indirection.
- Added 6 Failed Attempts rows (all tagged `unverified` / PLANNING): trusting the issue's `__all__` claim, deduping the two warning layers, one-shot test without cache reset, treating the change as additive, skipping the prose doc, and reusing `stacklevel=2` blindly.
