### Why

The lazy-exports section already taught the `__getattr__` / `_LAZY_IMPORTS` seam, but covered widening a surface, not retrofitting a deprecation warning onto a shim resolved by that seam. Issue #1545's planning surfaced five durable, non-obvious traps that share this skill's exact search surface (`__getattr__`, lazy loader, deprecation): the issue can misname *where* the symbol lives (`_LAZY_IMPORTS` vs `__all__`); access-time and call-time warnings are complementary layers that must both be kept; PEP 562 caches the resolved name into module globals so the access warning fires once per process unless the test pops it; an existing regression test may document and tolerate the current silent resolve and must be rewritten (a change is not additive if a green test encodes the old contract); and a prose doc (`COMPATIBILITY.md`) describing the warning as firing "when called" drifts unless updated in the same PR. The plan was never executed, so all material is `unverified` and the new workflow is titled "Proposed Workflow" with a warning banner.

